	     Millions of WhatsApp users have been left disconnected after the popular messaging app seemed to shut down on Friday morning. Frustrated WhatsAppers took to social media to express frustration, unable to send or receive messages. According to Metro.co.uk, it’s not clear how bad the outage is, but it appears to be affecting users all over the world. DownDetector, which tracks reports of apps and services not working, says thousands of users have been reporting issues since 8 am this morning. According to the site, 60 percent of users are having trouble connecting.    Sources: Express.co.uk, Metro.co.uk, DownDetector, Daily Star   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  